messages.content: Count how many resumes have stanford university

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.resume_id) AS num_resumes FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_College" rc ON r.resume_id = rc.resume_id JOIN "College" c ON rc.college_id = c.college_id WHERE c.college_name = 'stanford university';
Find all applicants with no job experience
SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r LEFT JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id WHERE e.resume_id IS NULL;
List the resumes with skills in Linux, Ubuntu, and Docker

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id IN (SELECT rs1.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs1 JOIN "Skills" s1 ON rs1.skill_id = s1.skill_id WHERE s1.skill_name = 'Linux' INTERSECT SELECT rs2.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs2 JOIN "Skills" s2 ON rs2.skill_id = s2.skill_id WHERE s2.skill_name = 'Ubuntu' INTERSECT SELECT rs3.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs3 JOIN "Skills" s3 ON rs3.skill_id = s3.skill_id WHERE s3.skill_name = 'Docker');
Find all resumes that have both python and java as a skill

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs1 ON r.resume_id = rs1.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s1 ON rs1.skill_id = s1.skill_id AND s1.skill_name = 'Python' JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs2 ON r.resume_id = rs2.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s2 ON rs2.skill_id = s2.skill_id AND s2.skill_name = 'Java';
How many applicants have experience in sales and marketing

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.resume_id) AS num_applicants FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id IN (SELECT rs.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('Sales', 'Marketing') GROUP BY rs.resume_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT s.skill_name) = 2) OR r.resume_id IN (SELECT e.resume_id FROM "Experience" e JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE (jt.title_name ILIKE '%sales%') AND (jt.title_name ILIKE '%marketing%'));
Find all resumes with senior-level positions

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE jt.title_name ILIKE '%senior%';
Get me applicants with a law degree

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_College" rc ON r.resume_id = rc.resume_id JOIN "Degree" d ON rc.degree_id = d.degree_id WHERE d.degree_name ILIKE '%law%' or d.degree_name ILIKE '%j.d%';
Get resumes of applicants who have experience in software development and system administration.

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id IN (SELECT rs1.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs1 JOIN "Skills" s1 ON rs1.skill_id = s1.skill_id WHERE s1.skill_name = 'Software Development' INTERSECT SELECT rs2.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs2 JOIN "Skills" s2 ON rs2.skill_id = s2.skill_id WHERE s2.skill_name = 'System Administration');
Get me applicants with a phd degree

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_College" rc ON r.resume_id = rc.resume_id JOIN "Degree" d ON rc.degree_id = d.degree_id WHERE d.degree_name ILIKE '%phd%' OR d.degree_name ILIKE '%doctorate%';
Get resumes of applicants proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, Powerpoint, or Outlook

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('word', 'excel', 'powerpoint', 'outlook');
Get all resumes with at least one former job

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text, COUNT(e.experience_id) as experience_count FROM "Resume" as r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id GROUP BY r.resume_id HAVING COUNT(e.experience_id) > 0;
Find all applicants who worked at at&t
SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id JOIN "Company" c ON e.company_id = c.company_id WHERE c.company_name = 'AT&T';
List all resumes of applicants who worked as product managers

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE jt.title_name ILIKE '%product manager%' OR jt.title_name ILIKE '%product management%';
Retrieve resumes that have problem solving as a skill
SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name = 'Problem Solving';
Get resumes containing both communication and teamwork skills

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id IN (SELECT rs.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('communication', 'teamwork') GROUP BY rs.resume_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT s.skill_name) = 2);
How many applicants have experience in both Java and Python

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.resume_id) AS num_applicants FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id IN ( SELECT rs.resume_id FROM "Resume_Skill" rs JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('java', 'python') GROUP BY rs.resume_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT s.skill_name) = 2) OR r.resume_id IN (SELECT e.resume_id FROM "Experience" e JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE jt.title_name ILIKE '%java%' AND jt.title_name ILIKE '%python%');
Find resumes with automation or scripting skills
SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('automation', 'scripting');
Find resumes with foriegn language experience in Spanish, French, or German

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('spanish', 'french', 'german');
List all applicants with skills related to web devlepment skills like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, or Angular

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('html', 'css', 'javascript', 'react', 'angular');
Get me applicants with a master's degree

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_College" rc ON r.resume_id = rc.resume_id JOIN "Degree" d ON rc.degree_id = d.degree_id WHERE d.degree_name ILIKE '%master%' OR d.degree_name ILIKE '%m.s.%';
Find all project managers

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE jt.title_name ILIKE '%project manager%' OR jt.title_name ILIKE '%project management%';
Find resumes of candidates who did not work at a company name

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id NOT IN (SELECT e.resume_id FROM "Experience" e JOIN "Company" c ON e.company_id = c.company_id WHERE c.company_name = 'Company Name');
Find applicants who graduated from northwestern university

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_College" rc ON r.resume_id = rc.resume_id JOIN "College" c ON rc.college_id = c.college_id WHERE c.college_name = 'northwestern university';
Find all vice president applicants

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE jt.title_name ILIKE '%vice president%' OR jt.title_name ILIKE '%v.p.%';
